<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q11_v7" title="Q11_v7" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>Para analizar el rendimiento de un atleta se describe la siguiente relación:</p>
    <div>
      <p>En cada segundo de carrera, el atleta avanza <m:math><m:mn>4000</m:mn></m:math> centímetros. Para calcular la distancia recorrida en centímetros, se multiplica el número de segundos por <m:math><m:mn>4000</m:mn></m:math>.</p>
    </div>
    <p>Si el atleta corre durante <m:math><m:mn>45</m:mn></m:math> segundos y se sabe que <m:math><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:math> metro equivale a <m:math><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:math> centímetros, ¿cuántos metros recorre en total?</p>
    <p>Elige una opción.</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" max-choices="1">
      <qti-prompt>Selecciona la cantidad de metros que recorre el atleta.</qti-prompt>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">180 metros<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La distancia total es 4000 × 45 = 180 000 centímetros. Como 1 metro = 100 centímetros, entonces 180 000 ÷ 100 = 1800 metros. Por eso, 180 metros no corresponde al problema.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">1 800 metros<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! La distancia total es 4000 × 45 = 180 000 centímetros. Luego, como 1 metro = 100 centímetros, se convierte así: 180 000 ÷ 100 = 1800 metros.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">18 000 000 metros<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La multiplicación correcta es 4000 × 45 = 180 000 centímetros, no 18 000 000. Después, al pasar de centímetros a metros se divide por 100: 180 000 ÷ 100 = 1800 metros. Por eso, 18 000 000 metros no satisface el problema.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">40 metros<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. La distancia total es 4000 × 45 = 180 000 centímetros. Al convertir a metros, 180 000 ÷ 100 = 1800 metros. Entonces, 40 metros no coincide con la distancia recorrida.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Calcular la distancia en centímetros</strong></p>
            <p>El atleta avanza <m:math><m:mn>4000</m:mn></m:math> centímetros por cada segundo.</p>
            <p>En <m:math><m:mn>45</m:mn></m:math> segundos recorre:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>4000</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>×</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>45</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>180&#160;000</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
              centímetros.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Convertir centímetros a metros</strong></p>
            <p>Sabemos que:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> metro </m:mtext>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>100</m:mn>
                  <m:mtext> centímetros</m:mtext>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Entonces, para pasar de centímetros a metros, se divide por <m:math><m:mn>100</m:mn></m:math>:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>180&#160;000</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>÷</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>100</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>1800</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Concluir</strong></p>
            <p>La distancia total recorrida por el atleta es <strong>1 800 metros</strong>.</p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, la alternativa correcta es <strong>B) 1 800 metros</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>